HOUSE JOINT RESOLUTION 955
By Powell
A RESOLUTION to recognize the YMCA of Middle Tennessee on
the occasion of its 150th anniversary.
WHEREAS, it is fitting that the members of this General Assembly should recognize
those institutions and organizations of this State that strive to improve the lives of children and
families in their local communities; and
WHEREAS, one such noteworthy organization is the YMCA of Middle Tennessee, which
celebrated its 150th anniversary in July 2025; and
WHEREAS, since the opening of the first YMCA in downtown Nashville in 1875, the
YMCA of Middle Tennessee has grown and adapted to serve the needs of the community and
currently operates facilities in Bellevue, Brentwood, Clarksville, Donelson-Hermitage, downtown
Nashville, Franklin, Green Hills, East Nashville, Smyrna, North Nashville, Robertson County,
and Sumner County, as well as Camp Widjiwagan in Antioch; and
WHEREAS, the YMCA of Middle Tennessee is one of our finest assets, providing
families and people of all ages with a wide variety of programs designed to develop character,
achieve better mental and physical fitness, and build lasting and positive relationships with
peers; and
WHEREAS, for one and a half centuries, the YMCA of Middle Tennessee has served as
a wellness hub for individuals and families at every stage of life, and it is most appropriate that
we commend this exceptional organization for being a shining example of the very best that
YMCA clubs have to offer; now, therefore,
BE IT RESOLVED BY THE HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES OF THE ONE HUNDRED
FOURTEENTH GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF THE STATE OF TENNESSEE, THE SENATE
CONCURRING, that we honor and congratulate the leadership, staff, and members of the
